value.title: Democrat in Greenwich 'ecstatic' Kamala Harris on cusp of being VP
value.excerpt: Joe Biden seemed poised on Friday to take Pennsylvania and, most likely, the presidency. The victory, if and when it comes, was applauded by local experts.

value.title: AOC wants anti-Trump Lincoln Project to give money to those who 'actually' made a difference
value.excerpt: After the Democratic Party failed to meet its electoral expectations in House races around the country on Election Day, one New York Democrat urged a conservative political group to donate money to progressive organizations.

value.title: Joe Biden spoke about how Americans 'chose change over more of the same'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden spoke to his supporters in Wilmington, Delaware about how Americans "want the country to come together and not be pulled apart."

value.title: Biden claims 'mandate' while election vs. Trump remains undecided
value.excerpt: Joe Biden didn't declare victory Friday night over President Trump in the race for the White House, but he emphasized that he's "going to win" the presidential election.

value.title: Bolsonaro abandons 'friend' Trump after 2020 election, says he's 'not the most important person in the world'

value.title: Bernie Sanders thanks, praises progressives for 'Biden's victory' before race is called
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders thanked progressives Friday afternoon for aiding Democratic nominee Joe Biden’s 2020 presidential efforts – even with the race still too close to call.

value.title: Trump's spiritual advisor Paula White speaks in tongues during a prayer broadcast to defeat the president's opponents
value.excerpt: In her prayer performance, Paula White claimed that "demonic confederacies" were "attempting to steal the election from Trump."

value.title: GOP to argue Georgia Senate runoffs would be key to check Biden and a Democratic House
value.excerpt: Georgia Republican Sens. David Perdue and Kelly Loeffler are bracing for a two-month slog in Georgia that could determine the next Senate majority, planning to argue that they need to keep their seats to prevent Democratic control of Washington.

value.title: Why Arizona’s Storied Conservative Stronghold Could Flip for Biden
value.excerpt: Maricopa County spawned the careers of Republican hard-liners like Joe Arpaio. Now the children of immigrants targeted in the state’s nativist crackdown are challenging G.O.P. dominance.

value.title: Doctors say they’re ‘hopeful’ Biden will handle the pandemic better, but ‘disappointed’ that he didn’t win by a landslide
value.excerpt: Three doctors spoke to Insider about the projection that Joe Biden has won the election, and what could happen next.

value.title: Kamala Harris in Detroit on Election Day to rally support: 'Have faith in the American people'
value.excerpt: Harris encouraged voters to trust their neighbors and the electoral process before canvassing throughout metro Detroit.

value.title: Minnesota 'Squad' member says Trump attack on her during campaign was a mistake
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., on Thursday said Trump "effed around" in deciding to attack her as a way to win over Minnesota voters.

value.title: Trump campaign hasn't provided evidence to back up claim of Wisconsin election 'irregularities'
value.excerpt: Trump and officials with his campaign have floated vague accusations with no evidence of election tampering in Wisconsin.

value.title: Trump and GOP lawsuits thus far challenging few ballots with no proof of fraud
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and the Republican National Committee's vows to challenge the election results and win through the courts appear unlikely to be successful with so few ballots at issue in litigation to make any difference in enough states to matter.

value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Trump 'likely' to run again in 2024 if he loses: Mick Mulvaney
value.excerpt: Trump's former acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney says the president isn't ready to bow out of politics.

value.title: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey says Trump's claims of 'large-scale fraud and theft of the election are just not substantiated'
value.excerpt: Following Trump's claims of voter fraud and theft, Republican officials and former Trump associates are in disagreement.

value.title: If Trump loses, he will regret 'denigrating mail-in voting': York
value.excerpt: If President Trump loses the election to Joe Biden as current vote tallies indicate, he could regret warning against mail-in voting, Fox News contributor Byron York argued Friday.

value.title: Trump investment in North Carolina's Native American Lumbee Tribe pays off
value.excerpt: Robeson County voters chose Trump (59%) over Democratic nominee Joe Biden (41%) after Trump held a rally there on Oct. 24, according to preliminary data.

value.title: Secret Service to dispatch extra protection squad to Joe Biden's campaign headquarters in Delaware
value.excerpt: The extra security will be assigned to the Wilmington Convention Center, Delaware, where the Biden campaign is headquartered.

value.title: Federal judge dismisses Trump request to stop counting Philadelphia ballots
value.excerpt: A federal judge reportedly dismissed an emergency injunction brought by the Trump campaign Thursday afternoon to stop the counting of votes in Philadelphia, claiming election workers were ignoring an earlier court ruling over election observers.

value.title: Kevin McCarthy echoed Trump's false claim that he won the election, saying Republicans 'will not back down'
value.excerpt: "President Trump won this election, so everyone who's listening, do not be quiet," McCarthy said. Trump has not won the election.

value.title: Trump's voter-fraud remarks draw criticism from some Republicans
